⚠️ 5. One tiny grammar improvement (optional)
You wrote:
This world features () shaped by ().



⚠️ 4. Optional polish (not required)
If you want slightly more natural phrasing, you could capitalize the first letter of each sentence fragment:


⚠️ 5. Minor optional improvement
If a table entry is something like Westerlies or Westward Drift, your .includes(West) logic still works — which is great.
But if you ever add more complex wind models, you might want to normalize the strings:
const wind = we.primary.toLowerCase();
if (wind.includes(west)) ...



Region Names —could be more varied
So you get names like:
Mountain Ancient Coast
Mountain Ancient Highlands
These are fine, but you could get more variety by:
using .twist sometimes
using random syllables
using biome based names
using elevation based names


Pick Biome
This is fine for region level flavor text, but note:
❗ It does not match your hex map biome logic.
Your hex map uses:
latitude
elevation
moisture
tectonics
hydrology
noise variation
This region generator uses only seed level parameters.
That’s okay — region summaries are high level flavor, not simulation — but it’s worth noting.


