Example Region Output
Name: The Silver Steppe Type: Steppe Country Biome: Temperate Grassland Elevation: Rolling Highlands Moisture: Seasonal Rains Climate Pattern: Cold air drainage valleys Sub Features: a deep limestone gorge; a chain of crater lakes Special Feature: Ancient ley line scars Narrative Hook: Hunters claim the forest moves at night. Short Description: A windswept expanse of rolling highlands shaped by cold air drainage valleys. Seasonal rains feed a deep limestone gorge and a chain of crater lakes. Ancient ley line scars cut across the land, and locals whisper that the nearby forest moves after dusk.

